article.headline: N.C. Central 66, W. Illinois 58
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- C.J. Wilkerson scored 25 points to pace North Carolina Central to a 66-58 nonconference victory over Western Illinois on Wednesday night. Landon Clement added 21 points and Nick Chasten 12 for the Eagles (9-9), who have won four of their last five games. Kaimarr Price scored 20 points for the Leathernecks (7-13), who lost their third in a row and sixth in their last seven. Brandon Smith scored 13, including three 3-pointers, and Matt Lander had 12. Jelani Johnson grabbed a game-best eight rebounds. Trailing 7-5, the Eagles went on an 11-0 run, all but two by Wilkerson, to make it 16-7 with 10 minutes left in the first half. They led 29-22 at intermission, and the lead peaked at 35-22 early in the second half. Wilkerson has scored 119 points his last four games.
